Detailed Project Report (DPR)


Introduction  : 

The To-Do List Application is a minimalistic web application designed to help users manage their tasks efficiently. The application provides functionality for adding and deleting tasks with a clean and user-friendly interface.

Objectives  : 

To create a web-based to-do list application.
To provide a simple interface for task management.
To ensure ease of use with minimalistic design.

Functional Requirements  :

Add Task: The user can add a new task to the to-do list.
Delete Task: The user can delete a task from the to-do list.

Non-Functional Requirements  :

Usability: The application should be easy to use with a clean interface.
Performance: The application should load quickly and respond promptly to user actions.
Compatibility: The application should work on modern web browsers.

Design and Architecture  :

Frontend: HTML is used for the structure, CSS for styling, and JavaScript for interactivity.
No Backend: The application does not require a backend or database as it handles tasks within the client-side session.

Implementation Details  :

The application is implemented using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
The CSS provides a modern and clean look using the Poppins font family.
JavaScript is used to handle the addition and deletion of tasks dynamically.

Testing  :

Unit Testing: Each function (add, delete) was tested independently.
Integration Testing: The application was tested as a whole to ensure all components work together seamlessly.
User Acceptance Testing: The application was tested by users to ensure it meets their needs and expectations.

Conclusion  :

The To-Do List Application is a simple, effective tool for managing tasks. It is designed with usability in mind and provides all the basic functionalities required for a to-do list application.
